parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Continuously Variable Transmission (CVT) can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or fail to accelerate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when accelerating
the engine RPMs increase without corresponding acceleration
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle makes a loud whining or grinding noise
and the "Service Vehicle Soon" or "Check Engine" warning light is illuminated.
